Hundreds of young men arm with guns have invaded Danancha village in Gasol Local government area of Taraba state kill two persons, burn over hundred houses with properties worth millions of naira and displace residents. The gunmen invaded the village at about 3pm and started burning the houses, shooting sporadically without any provocation from any of the residents. Danancha has been under attacks between Tiv and Jukuns since the renaming of the village by Taraba state government from Danancha to Kwararafa village. a joint security operatives were deployed and stationed in the village to keep the peace among the people. The former special assistant to governor Darius Ishaku of Taraba Hon. Jerry Tyolanga who is a resident of Dananacha told LEADERSHIP via telephone that several houses were burnt with properties worth millions of naira while two persons were found dead with bullet wounds. It was also gathered the gunmen carried out the destruction from 3pm to 6pm without been interrupted by the joint security forces that have been stationed in the village. Another resident of Dananacha Mr. Jaspa Danu while speaking with our correspondent said normalcy has returned in the village as more military forces were deployed to the area to control the situation. Phone numbers of the caretaker chairman of Gasol local government council Hon. Tanko Maikerfi were off at the time of the report when he was called to comment on the incident. Even though LEADERSHIP witnessed massive exodus of the villagers who were running to take refuge in Jalingo the state capital, the police public relation officer (PPRO) Taraba state command DSP David Misar while contacted over the incident said he was yet to be briefed by the DPO of the Danancha.